<h2 style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #a78e6b; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 24px;">Do you know a parent like this?</h2>
<blockquote style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #363561; font-size: 11px; font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 24px; font-style: italic; padding-top: 0px; padding-right: 15px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 15px;">&ldquo;We didn&rsquo;t get serious about the college admissions planning process until our son&rsquo;s junior year. And through sad experience, we learned that his study habits, grades, and extracurricular activities weren&rsquo;t strong enough to get him into the colleges we wanted him to attend. We should have started way back in the eighth or ninth grade!"</blockquote>
<h2 style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #a78e6b; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 24px;">College Vision was established to help parents successfully get their high school students on track and into college.</h2>
